1283 - Find the Smallest Divisor Given a Threshold
Problem Summary

Given an array nums and an integer threshold, find the smallest positive divisor such that:

sum(ceil(nums[i] / divisor)) <= threshold
Key Observation

As the divisor increases, the value of:

ceil(nums[i] / divisor)

either:

decreases
remains the same

Therefore, the total sum is monotonically decreasing.

Example:

nums = [1,2,5,9]

divisor = 1 → sum = 17
divisor = 2 → sum = 10
divisor = 3 → sum = 7
divisor = 4 → sum = 7
divisor = 5 → sum = 5
17 → 10 → 7 → 7 → 5

The sum never increases.

Binary Search on Answer

Possible divisors lie in the range:

[1, max(nums)]

For some divisor values, the condition fails:

NO NO NO NO YES YES YES YES

Once a divisor satisfies:

sum <= threshold

all larger divisors will also satisfy it.

This monotonic pattern makes Binary Search applicable.

Search Space
int low = 1;
int high = max(nums);
Mid Calculation
int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
Validity Check

For a chosen divisor:

sum += ceil(nums[i] / divisor);

If:

sum <= threshold

the divisor works, so try finding a smaller one:

high = mid - 1;

Otherwise:

low = mid + 1;
Ceiling Division Trick

Instead of:

Math.ceil((double) num / divisor)

use integer arithmetic:

(num + divisor - 1) / divisor

Example:

9 / 5 = 1.8
ceil(1.8) = 2

(9 + 5 - 1) / 5
= 13 / 5
= 2
Algorithm
Set low = 1, high = max(nums).
While low <= high:
Compute mid.
Calculate the sum using ceiling division.
If sum <= threshold:
Search left half (high = mid - 1).
Else:
Search right half (low = mid + 1).
Return low.
Java Solution
class Solution {
    public int smallestDivisor(int[] nums, int threshold) {

        int low = 1;
        int high = 0;

        for (int num : nums) {
            high = Math.max(high, num);
        }

        while (low <= high) {

            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            long sum = 0;

            for (int num : nums) {
                sum += (num + mid - 1) / mid;
            }

            if (sum <= threshold) {
                high = mid - 1;
            } else {
                low = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return low;
    }
}
Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity

Finding the sum for one divisor:

O(n)

Binary search over:

[1, max(nums)]

takes:

O(log(max(nums)))

Overall:

O(n × log(max(nums)))
Space Complexity
O(1)
Pattern Recognition

Use Binary Search on Answer when:

Asked to find the minimum/maximum value satisfying a condition.
The condition forms a monotonic pattern:
NO NO NO YES YES YES

or

YES YES YES NO NO NO
